-- Citigroup Names DeKuyper, Fukada for Investment-Banking Posts in Calgary
-- Doug Alexander
-- 2010-07-14T21:36:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/citigroup-names-dekuyper-fukada-for-investment-banking-posts-in-calgary.html

          
          
             Citigroup Inc. ’s Canadian arm named
Gordon DeKuyper and Kasey Fukada to help run investment banking
operations in Calgary.  
 DeKuyper, previously in a corporate banking role in Hong
Kong, is the unit’s new managing director of global banking,
according to an e-mailed statement sent today from Citigroup.
Fukada, who held roles at Toronto-Dominion Bank’s  TD Securities 
and Royal Bank of Canada’s RBC Capital Markets, was hired as
director of investment banking.  
 Citigroup has about 10 investment bankers in Calgary. The
New York-based lender has about 4,600 employees in Canada.  
